Logistics

Partners

We have identified three operational partners:

  • GEOBON-International experts. This group will present which models and tools are available within the GEO BON international community aimed to measure, assess and monitor co-benefits of ecosystem services derived from carbon storage and biodiversity.

  • Regional experts. This group will provide an evaluation whether:

    • are these models and tools presented feasible to apply in this region?

    • are data sets currently available are enough for applying proposed models and tools?

  • Implementers/users: PC, ECCC, Indigenous partners, Provincial (MB, ON, QC). This group will respond among others these questions:

    • How can we implement, use proposed models and tools?

    • What are the pros, cons, trade-offs and assumptions.

    • What can be done now (tactical) and in the future?

    • How can we inform conservation decisions based on the best available data?

Workshop

We will held a workshop with all partners.

  • Date: October 16 and 17, 2023 (Monday and Tuesday)

  • Place and venue: Montreal (venue TBD)

We are planning to have breaking/discussion groups for specific topics that will report in plenary sessions. This is a preliminary list that is not in a specific order yet:

Topic
1 Carbon storage: how to measure it
2 Carbon storage: services provided
3 Traditional food security (freshwater fisheries, wild foods)
4 Integrating knowledge systems
5 Protecting genetic diversity
6 Protecting species/communities
7 Protecting ecosystems
8 Multiple/dual frameworks
9 Prioritization tools
10 Integrating models/tools/indicators
